Sage advice from Gozaro of Iron Monkey.  This is the raid guide unless he changes it in South Ro.<br>
<br>
----------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Hi guys,<br>
<br>
I was asked by Tpar to come to he forum and offer some advice and maybe help you tomorrow if you wish.<br>
At any rate here is what I know so far about the NEW hate. I haven't tried our old strategy for breaking it. I've heard it won't work, but I always check things for myself .. haha..<br>
<br>
For now, as far as I know, you MUST break hate from the zone in. This isn't to hard, but it's VERY important that you know exactly what to do and expect when you zone in.<br>
<br>
I've made a few illustrations of where I like people to stand and fight when we break from the zone.<br>
Also the break in is important too. If anyone goofs up when we zone up it could mean 4-5 mobs on top of you and unless you are prepared you will get wiped out.<br>
<br>
If it comes down to it, just evac out. If you can kill one or two mobs every trip at least you will eventually get settled in and only have to deal with roamers.<br>
<br>
Here are the two pictures. I'll post more details below on gating up and groups and agro.. etc..<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
How to gate up:<br>
- Make good groups because you might have to fight when you gate up.<br>
- Make groups of 5 unless you have more then one wizard to gate each group up individually.<br>
- Fully buff and get FM<br>
- Invis and gate up.<br>
- Take 5 steps backwards when you zone in and do not move or touch the walls. <br>
- Wait for 2nd and 3rd group to gate up.<br>
- 4th 5th or more groups don't come up until any roaming mobs that attack are killed or it looks like everything is under control.<br>
<br>
Fighting in the first building:<br>
Basically everyone stays in the building. The enchanters go outside the door.<br>
The monk will pull to the Feign spot and the pulling tank will pull from the monk to the enchanters area. The enchanters will mez the mobs they want and the tank will pull the one to engage into the building.<br>
Bring shrink potions!!! you have been warned =)<br>
<br>
Very important Hate Rules:<br>
- Do not leave the building. Only the enchanters, pulling tank and monk should leave the building.<br>
- Dispell Spite golems 5 times to remove their sow, and do not attempt to cast or debuff them<br>
- Mez Male Revenents before Females<br>
- Attack priorities Spites first, Clerics 2nd, Female Revenants 3rd.<br>
- Dispel everything at the beginning of the fight.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
some extra junk...<br>
<br>
My raid group Philosophies:<br>
I use some basic rules when making groups for a big raid.<br>
1. Groups are made for mana efficiency with the purpose of winning, not for experience.<br>
2. Each enchanter has a dedicated healer. Preferably a cleric =)<br>
3. Bards can never be in the pull group because their song may hit the pulling monk before he Feigns killing everyone =)<br>
4. Never put your highest damage taking tank in the same group with puller or enchanter. two reasons. It takes way to much mana to heal al those people and one cleric may not be able to keep them both alive.<br>
5. Shaman's, enchanters and wizards should have priority for bard groups.<br>
<br>
Pull group - Monk, Cleric, Druid and anyone else that won't agro or be noticed much at all. 3 is fine too<br>
Tank Group - Heavy on hps and high agro tanks - 1 or 2 clerics, bards are ok if you have extra<br>
Support and caster groups.<br>
Clerics or druid/shaman in each. Anyone with high agro should be with a cleric. 1 healer per enchanter.<br>
Bard groups should always be FULL regardless of the number of people on the raid because of manasong.<br>
<br>
Be sure to assign someone to dispel, slow, snare.<br>
Assign a Primary Assist and a Secondary. Sometimes I tell people who to assist and then have that person assist the &quot;secret primary&quot; =) This prevents a lot of problems haha<br>
<br>
